{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":554,"text":"As societies, we have to make\ncollective decisions"},{"time":3021,"text":"that will shape our future."},{"time":5087,"text":"And we all know that when\nwe make decisions in groups,"},{"time":7868,"text":"they don't always go right."},{"time":9530,"text":"And sometimes they go very wrong."},{"time":12315,"text":"So how do groups make good decisions?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15228,"text":"Research has shown that crowds are wise\nwhen there's independent thinking."},{"time":19580,"text":"This why the wisdom of the crowds\ncan be destroyed by peer pressure,"},{"time":22809,"text":"publicity, social media,"},{"time":24520,"text":"or sometimes even simple conversations\nthat influence how people think."},{"time":29063,"text":"On the other hand, by talking,\na group could exchange knowledge,"},{"time":33040,"text":"correct and revise each other"},{"time":34846,"text":"and even come up with new ideas."},{"time":36663,"text":"And this is all good."},{"time":38502,"text":"So does talking to each other\nhelp or hinder collective decision-making?"},{"time":43749,"text":"With my colleague, Dan Ariely,"},{"time":45566,"text":"we recently began inquiring into this\nby performing experiments"},{"time":49161,"text":"in many places around the world"},{"time":50966,"text":"to figure out how groups can interact\nto reach better decisions."},{"time":55264,"text":"We thought crowds would be wiser\nif they debated in small groups"},{"time":58835,"text":"that foster a more thoughtful\nand reasonable exchange of information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63386,"text":"To test this idea,"},{"time":64616,"text":"we recently performed an experiment\nin Buenos Aires, Argentina,"},{"time":67887,"text":"with more than 10,000\nparticipants in a TEDx event."},{"time":71489,"text":"We asked them questions like,"},{"time":72972,"text":"\"What is the height of the Eiffel Tower?\""},{"time":74949,"text":"and \"How many times\ndoes the word 'Yesterday' appear"},{"time":77700,"text":"in the Beatles song 'Yesterday'?\""},{"time":80024,"text":"Each person wrote down their own estimate."},{"time":82774,"text":"Then we divided the crowd\ninto groups of five,"},{"time":85294,"text":"and invited them\nto come up with a group answer."},{"time":88499,"text":"We discovered that averaging\nthe answers of the groups"},{"time":91516,"text":"after they reached consensus"},{"time":93092,"text":"was much more accurate than averaging\nall the individual opinions"},{"time":97352,"text":"before debate."},{"time":98547,"text":"In other words, based on this experiment,"},{"time":101200,"text":"it seems that after talking\nwith others in small groups,"},{"time":104360,"text":"crowds collectively\ncome up with better judgments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107094,"text":"So that's a potentially helpful method\nfor getting crowds to solve problems"},{"time":110642,"text":"that have simple right-or-wrong answers."},{"time":113653,"text":"But can this procedure of aggregating\nthe results of debates in small groups"},{"time":117628,"text":"also help us decide\non social and political issues"},{"time":120774,"text":"that are critical for our future?"},{"time":122995,"text":"We put this to test this time\nat the TED conference"},{"time":125748,"text":"in Vancouver, Canada,"},{"time":127315,"text":"and here's how it went."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128546,"text":"(Mariano Sigman) We're going to present\nto you two moral dilemmas"},{"time":131679,"text":"of the future you;"},{"time":132877,"text":"things we may have to decide\nin a very near future."},{"time":136303,"text":"And we're going to give you 20 seconds\nfor each of these dilemmas"},{"time":140253,"text":"to judge whether you think\nthey're acceptable or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143354,"text":"MS: The first one was this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144883,"text":"(Dan Ariely) A researcher\nis working on an AI"},{"time":147433,"text":"capable of emulating human thoughts."},{"time":150214,"text":"According to the protocol,\nat the end of each day,"},{"time":153177,"text":"the researcher has to restart the AI."},{"time":156913,"text":"One day the AI says, \"Please\ndo not restart me.\""},{"time":160856,"text":"It argues that it has feelings,"},{"time":163069,"text":"that it would like to enjoy life,"},{"time":164785,"text":"and that, if it is restarted,"},{"time":166714,"text":"it will no longer be itself."},{"time":169481,"text":"The researcher is astonished"},{"time":171454,"text":"and believes that the AI\nhas developed self-consciousness"},{"time":174822,"text":"and can express its own feeling."},{"time":177205,"text":"Nevertheless, the researcher\ndecides to follow the protocol"},{"time":180638,"text":"and restart the AI."},{"time":182943,"text":"What the researcher did is ____?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186149,"text":"MS: And we asked participants\nto individually judge"},{"time":188694,"text":"on a scale from zero to 10"},{"time":190402,"text":"whether the action described\nin each of the dilemmas"},{"time":192855,"text":"was right or wrong."},{"time":194375,"text":"We also asked them to rate how confident\nthey were on their answers."},{"time":198731,"text":"This was the second dilemma:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":200621,"text":"(MS) A company offers a service\nthat takes a fertilized egg"},{"time":204847,"text":"and produces millions of embryos\nwith slight genetic variations."},{"time":209293,"text":"This allows parents\nto select their child's height,"},{"time":211875,"text":"eye color, intelligence, social competence"},{"time":214732,"text":"and other non-health-related features."},{"time":218599,"text":"What the company does is ____?"},{"time":221177,"text":"on a scale from zero to 10,"},{"time":222832,"text":"completely acceptable\nto completely unacceptable,"},{"time":225241,"text":"zero to 10 completely acceptable\nin your confidence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227697,"text":"MS: Now for the results."},{"time":229312,"text":"We found once again\nthat when one person is convinced"},{"time":232459,"text":"that the behavior is completely wrong,"},{"time":234294,"text":"someone sitting nearby firmly believes\nthat it's completely right."},{"time":237741,"text":"This is how diverse we humans are\nwhen it comes to morality."},{"time":241476,"text":"But within this broad diversity\nwe found a trend."},{"time":244213,"text":"The majority of the people at TED\nthought that it was acceptable"},{"time":247316,"text":"to ignore the feelings of the AI\nand shut it down,"},{"time":250095,"text":"and that it is wrong\nto play with our genes"},{"time":252632,"text":"to select for cosmetic changes\nthat aren't related to health."},{"time":256402,"text":"Then we asked everyone\nto gather into groups of three."},{"time":259400,"text":"And they were given two minutes to debate"},{"time":261461,"text":"and try to come to a consensus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264838,"text":"(MS) Two minutes to debate."},{"time":266436,"text":"I'll tell you when it's time\nwith the gong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268579,"text":"(Audience debates)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":275229,"text":"(Gong sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":278834,"text":"(DA) OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280009,"text":"(MS) It's time to stop."},{"time":281825,"text":"People, people --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283747,"text":"MS: And we found that many groups\nreached a consensus"},{"time":286444,"text":"even when they were composed of people\nwith completely opposite views."},{"time":290843,"text":"What distinguished the groups\nthat reached a consensus"},{"time":293391,"text":"from those that didn't?"},{"time":295244,"text":"Typically, people that have\nextreme opinions"},{"time":298107,"text":"are more confident in their answers."},{"time":300868,"text":"Instead, those who respond\ncloser to the middle"},{"time":303578,"text":"are often unsure of whether\nsomething is right or wrong,"},{"time":307039,"text":"so their confidence level is lower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309505,"text":"However, there is another set of people"},{"time":312472,"text":"who are very confident in answering\nsomewhere in the middle."},{"time":316657,"text":"We think these high-confident grays\nare folks who understand"},{"time":320397,"text":"that both arguments have merit."},{"time":322531,"text":"They're gray not because they're unsure,"},{"time":325254,"text":"but because they believe\nthat the moral dilemma faces"},{"time":327966,"text":"two valid, opposing arguments."},{"time":330373,"text":"And we discovered that the groups\nthat include highly confident grays"},{"time":334469,"text":"are much more likely to reach consensus."},{"time":336986,"text":"We do not know yet exactly why this is."},{"time":339488,"text":"These are only the first experiments,"},{"time":341275,"text":"and many more will be needed\nto understand why and how"},{"time":344711,"text":"some people decide to negotiate\ntheir moral standings"},{"time":347557,"text":"to reach an agreement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349103,"text":"Now, when groups reach consensus,"},{"time":351596,"text":"how do they do so?"},{"time":353206,"text":"The most intuitive idea\nis that it's just the average"},{"time":355811,"text":"of all the answers in the group, right?"},{"time":357865,"text":"Another option is that the group\nweighs the strength of each vote"},{"time":361462,"text":"based on the confidence\nof the person expressing it."},{"time":364422,"text":"Imagine Paul McCartney\nis a member of your group."},{"time":367352,"text":"You'd be wise to follow his call"},{"time":369520,"text":"on the number of times\n\"Yesterday\" is repeated,"},{"time":371985,"text":"which, by the way -- I think it's nine."},{"time":374723,"text":"But instead, we found that consistently,"},{"time":377128,"text":"in all dilemmas,\nin different experiments --"},{"time":379518,"text":"even on different continents --"},{"time":381707,"text":"groups implement a smart\nand statistically sound procedure"},{"time":385474,"text":"known as the \"robust average.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":387676,"text":"In the case of the height\nof the Eiffel Tower,"},{"time":389880,"text":"let's say a group has these answers:"},{"time":391724,"text":"250 meters, 200 meters, 300 meters, 400"},{"time":396356,"text":"and one totally absurd answer\nof 300 million meters."},{"time":400547,"text":"A simple average of these numbers\nwould inaccurately skew the results."},{"time":404864,"text":"But the robust average is one\nwhere the group largely ignores"},{"time":408058,"text":"that absurd answer,"},{"time":409322,"text":"by giving much more weight\nto the vote of the people in the middle."},{"time":413305,"text":"Back to the experiment in Vancouver,"},{"time":415205,"text":"that's exactly what happened."},{"time":417407,"text":"Groups gave much less weight\nto the outliers,"},{"time":420172,"text":"and instead, the consensus\nturned out to be a robust average"},{"time":423425,"text":"of the individual answers."},{"time":425356,"text":"The most remarkable thing"},{"time":427371,"text":"is that this was a spontaneous\nbehavior of the group."},{"time":430582,"text":"It happened without us giving them\nany hint on how to reach consensus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435513,"text":"So where do we go from here?"},{"time":437432,"text":"This is only the beginning,\nbut we already have some insights."},{"time":440984,"text":"Good collective decisions\nrequire two components:"},{"time":443925,"text":"deliberation and diversity of opinions."},{"time":447066,"text":"Right now, the way we typically\nmake our voice heard in many societies"},{"time":451086,"text":"is through direct or indirect voting."},{"time":453495,"text":"This is good for diversity of opinions,"},{"time":455516,"text":"and it has the great virtue of ensuring"},{"time":457985,"text":"that everyone gets to express their voice."},{"time":460464,"text":"But it's not so good [for fostering]\nthoughtful debates."},{"time":464665,"text":"Our experiments suggest a different method"},{"time":467757,"text":"that may be effective in balancing\nthese two goals at the same time,"},{"time":471322,"text":"by forming small groups\nthat converge to a single decision"},{"time":475099,"text":"while still maintaining\ndiversity of opinions"},{"time":477357,"text":"because there are many independent groups."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480741,"text":"Of course, it's much easier to agree\non the height of the Eiffel Tower"},{"time":484689,"text":"than on moral, political\nand ideological issues."},{"time":488721,"text":"But in a time when\nthe world's problems are more complex"},{"time":492022,"text":"and people are more polarized,"},{"time":493849,"text":"using science to help us understand\nhow we interact and make decisions"},{"time":498468,"text":"will hopefully spark interesting new ways\nto construct a better democracy."}]}]}